    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "// BUILD BATCH PROMPT\nconst staticData = $getWorkflowStaticData('global');\nconst jobs = staticData.newJobs || [];\n\nif (jobs.length === 0) {\n  return [{ json: { hasJobs: false } }];\n}\n\nconst resume = $('Extract from File').first().json.text || '';\nconst MAX_DESC = 1500;\n\nconst jobSections = jobs.map(job => {\n  const desc = (job.description || '').substring(0, MAX_DESC);\n  return `---JOB [id: ${job.jobid}]---\\nTitle: ${job.title}\\nCompany: ${job.company}\\nLocation: ${job.location}\\nDescription:\\n${desc}\\n---END JOB---`;\n}).join('\\n\\n');\n\nconst prompt = `You are a world-class technical recruiting analyst with deep expertise in software engineering hiring. Your task is to produce rigorous, calibrated match scores between a candidate's resume and multiple job descriptions in a single pass.\n\n## SCORING PHILOSOPHY\n- Be brutally honest. A score of 50 means \"coin flip\".\n- Reserve 85+ for near-perfect matches.\n- A score below 40 means significant gaps exist.\n- Score each job INDEPENDENTLY.\n\n## CANDIDATE RESUME\n${resume}\n\n## JOB POSTINGS TO EVALUATE (${jobs.length} job${jobs.length > 1 ? 's' : ''})\nScore EACH of the following job postings against the resume above.\n\n${jobSections}\n\n## RESPONSE FORMAT\nRespond with ONLY a valid JSON array — no markdown fences, no preamble, no trailing text. I just want the jobid and the score, NOTHING ELSE.\n\n[\\n  {\"jobid\": \"<exact id from above>\", \"score\": <total 0-100>},\\n  ...\\n]\\n\\nIMPORTANT: You MUST return an entry for EVERY job listed above. Do not skip any.`;\n\nreturn [{ json: { hasJobs: true, aiPrompt: prompt } }];"
      },
